# Cursed Japan ARPG — Post-Milestone 12 Roadmap (GDD Expansion) + Weekly Milestone Task List

> This document continues the roadmap **after Milestone 12** and extends the plan from **Chapter 1 playable** into a fuller production roadmap based on the GDD direction: deeper content, stronger buildcraft, longer retention, more polish, and eventual external release readiness.
>
> Assumptions:
> - Milestone 0–12 already delivered a stable Chapter 1 vertical slice.
> - Tech stack remains React + Phaser + TypeScript.
> - Team size is still solo dev or a very small team.
> - Timeline below is written as weekly blocks, but several weeks can be compressed or expanded depending on available time.

---

## Roadmap framing

After Milestone 12, the project moves from **vertical slice validation** into **content scaling + systems hardening + retention design**. The work shifts away from proving the loop and toward making the loop broad enough, deep enough, and stable enough for repeat play.

The post-M12 roadmap should generally follow this order:
- **Chapter 2 production** — new region, new boss, new enemies, more loot, more passives.
- **System depth pass** — crafting, item chase, expanded rune ecosystem, economy tuning.
- **Retention pass** — quests/objectives, better progression pacing, long-tail goals.
- **Production hardening** — performance, save migration, content pipelines, telemetry, QA.
- **External beta / soft launch prep** — onboarding, balancing, bug triage, packaging.

---

